<p>
In this method, we set \(x=t\) and \(t=t_{1}\) in the Volterra integral equation (3.1) to obtain \( u(t)=f(t)+\lambda \int_{0}^{x} K\left(t, t_{1}\right) u\left(t_{1}\right) d t_{1} \) Replacing \( u(t) \) in the RHS of the first equation.
</p>

<p>
<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=f(x)+\lambda \int_{0}^{x} K(x, t) u(t) d t+\lambda^{2} \int_{0}^{x} K(x, t) \int_{0}^{t} K\left(t, t_{1}\right) u\left(t_{1}\right) d t_{1} d t \)
</div>
</p>

<p>
Substituting \(x=t_{1}\) and \( t=t_{2} \), we find \( u\left(t_{1}\right)=f\left(t_{1}\right)+\lambda \int_{0}^{x} K\left(t_{1}, t_{2}\right) u\left(t_{2}\right) d t_{2} \)
</p>

<p>
Substituting \( u (t_{1}) \) in the previous equation yields;
</p>

<p>
<div class="l-example">
\( u(x)=f(x)+\lambda \int_{0}^{x} K(x, t) u(t) d t+\lambda^{2} \int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{t} K(x, t) K\left(t, t_{1}\right) u\left(t_{1}\right) d t_{1} d t+ \lambda^{3} \int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{t_{1} t_{2}} \int_{0}^{t} K(x, t) K\left(t, t_{1}\right) K\left(t_{1}, t_{2}\right) u\left(t_{2}\right) d t_{2} d t_{1} d t+\ldots \)
</div>
</p>

<p>
Remark here that, in this method the unknown function \(u(x)\) is substituted by the given function \( f(x) \) that makes the evaluation multiple integral easily computed. This substitution of \(u(x)\) occurs several times through the integrals and hence this is why it is called <b>successive substitution method</b>.
</p>

<div class="red bold">Example 3.4:</div>
<p>
Solve the Volterra integral equation \( u(x)=x-\int_{0}^{x}(x-t) u(t) d t \) using Successive Substitution Method (SSM).
</p>

<div class="red bold">Solution 3.4:</div>
<p>
    <div class="l-example">
    \( \lambda=-1, K(x, t)=x-t, K\left(t-t_{1}\right), f(x)=x, f(t)=t \)
    </div>
</p>
<p>
    <div class="l-example">
    \( u(x)=f(x)-\int_{0}^{x}(x-t) t \cdot d t+\int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{x}(x-t)\left(t-t_{1}\right) t_{1} d t_{1} d t+\ldots \)
    </div>
</p>
<p>
    <div class="l-example">
    \( u(x)=x-\int_{0}^{x}\left(x t-t^{2}\right) d t+\int_{0}^{x} \int_{0}^{t}\left(x t t_{1}-x t_{1}^{2}-t^{2} t_{1}+t t_{1}^{2}\right) d t_{1} d t+\ldots \)
    </div>
</p>
<p>
    <div class="l-example">
    \( u(x)=x-\left(\frac{x^{2}}{2}-\frac{x^{3}}{3}\right)+\int_{0}^{x}\left(\frac{x t^{3}}{2}-\frac{x t^{3}}{3}-\frac{t^{4}}{2}+\frac{t^{4}}{3}\right) d t+\ldots \)
    </div>
</p>
<p>
    <div class="l-example">
    \( u(x)=x-\frac{x t^{2}}{2}-\left.\frac{t^{3}}{3}\right|_{t=0} ^{x}+\left.\int_{0}^{x}\left(x t \frac{t_{1}^{2}}{2}-x \frac{t_{1}^{3}}{3}-t^{2} \frac{t_{1}^{2}}{2}+t \frac{t_{1}^{3}}{3}\right)\right|_{t_{1}-0} ^{t} d t+\ldots \)
    </div>
</p>
<p>
    <div class="l-example">
    \( u(x)=x-\frac{x^{3}}{6}+\left.\left(\frac{x t^{4}}{8}-\frac{x t^{4}}{12}-\frac{t^{3}}{10}+\frac{t^{5}}{15}\right)\right|_{i=0} ^{2}+\ldots \)
    </div>
</p>
<p>
    <div class="l-example">
    \( u(x)=x-\frac{x^{3}}{6}+\underset{(15)}{\frac{x t^{3}}{8}}-\underset{(10)}{\frac{x t^{3}}{12}}-\underset{(12)}{\frac{t^{3}}{10}}+\underset{(8)}{\frac{t^{3}}{15}}+\ldots \)
    </div>
</p>
<p>
    <div class="l-example">
    \( u(x)=\sin x  (\text {Taylor}) \)
    </div>
</p>